PLACE: Mainly Limassol, but whole island was affected
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Many stations recorded a 24hr rainfall which was well above the mean monthly for that station. e.g. Laneia 79.9mm vs. 23.1, Agios Mamas 67.3mm vs. 29, etc.  Roadways were flooded and closed to traffic for several hours. There were downslides of rocks and other debris in mountain regions that blocked roads on those areas. Power outages occured in some places and crops in heavily affected areas suffered extensive damages.

DETAILED_LOCATION: Mainly Nicosia town and suburbs, and nearby villages Geri, Tseri, Latsia, Dali.
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Roads and premises flooded. People trapped in vehicles and homes. Fire department intervened in many instances to save lives and properties. Vehicles were swept away in flash floods.In Tseri village the 24hr rain was 10 times the normal for June.

DETAILED_LOCATION: Mainly the town of Nicosia and suburbs, as well as nearby villages Latsia, Geri, Tseri, Dali.
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: At Tseri the recorded 24hr rainfall, 74.5mm was 10 times the mean monthly amount for June, 7.5mm.Similarly in other stations of the affected area.  Roadways and premises flooded, especially in Latsia, Geri, Tseri, Dali, Aglandjia. Fire department responded to almost 100 calls for help, such as to rescue kids trapped in football field, evacuation of flooded buildings and pumping water out of basements, restoring flooded and blocked roadways to traffic circulation, reopen congested drains and sewers for the drainage of rainwater, and to tow vehicles that were swept away in flash floods. The Civil Defense was called in to help in some situations.

Вчера вечером наибольшее количество осадков выпало на улице Полярной, там можно сказать, что было стихийное явление, потому что только за вечер, за два часа выпали 75 мм! В целом за ночь по Харькову количество осадков было около 20-30 мм: 4 мм на Рогани, на ул. Чернышевской – 36 мм, на Холодной горе – 30 мм. Норма же месячная для июня – 58 мм, - говорит Евгения Ляшенко, завсектором метеорологических прогнозов регионального гидрометцентра.

V oblasti Rajeckej doliny sa aktuálne vyskytujú už niekoľko desiatok minút veľmi intenzívne búrky. Bohužiaľ však v oblasti nie je umiestnená žiadna profesionálna ani amatérska zrážkomerná stanica, takže množstvo zrážok možno odhadovať len z radarových meraní. Na základe nich už v oblasti spadlo okolo 50 mm zrážok.

Jedna z najintenzívnejších búrok včerajšieho dňa sa vyskytla v Bratislave a juhovýchodne od hlavného mesta. V okolí Kvetoslavova sa vyskytla silná prietrž mračien, ktorá zaplavovala cesty a obce nechala bez elektrickej energie

EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Am Sonntagabend sorgte der viele Regen für Hangrutschungen und kleinere Murenabgänge in den Tamsweger Ortsteilen Lasaberg und Einöden.     Eine Mure verlegte Teile der Murtalbahn, die vorübergehend gesperrt werden musste.    Nach Mitternacht mussten die 30 Feuerwehrleute außerdem einen Parkplatz sichern und Montagfrüh einen Keller auspumpen.  Zeitpunkt geschätzt (RAD)

EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Ein Gewitter mit extrem starken, lokalen Regenschauern verursachte Verklausungen, Überflutungen von Straßen in Gallmannsegg und machte Hofzufahrtswege unpassierbar. Es kam auch zu Hangrutschungen.

CONTACT: Aktuelle Wetterwarnungen Österreich (AWÖ) | ILLAPA Unwetterwarnungen, Wetter- und Klimaforschung
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Mehreren Muren sind nach Unwettern in der Nacht auf Montag zwischen Mixnitz und Breitenau am Hochlantsch (Bezirk Bruck-Mürzzuschlag) in der Steiermark abgegangen und haben die Landesstraße verlegt. Vier Autos mit insgesamt acht Insassen wurden dabei eingeschlossen und die Feuerwehr musste sie retten. Außerdem war ein Bauernhof von einer Mure bedroht und wurde evakuiert.    Zeit verifiziert über FF-Einsatzprotokoll des LFV Stmk.

A thunderstorm with heavy rain occured in Kamienica and Zasadne villages and the neighboring Gorce mountains. CONTACT: Stalo Papachristodoulou; checked by satellite image and lightning detection by Thomas Schreiner, ESWD Quality Control
DETAILED_LOCATION: Town of Larnaca and surrounding areas. Limassol and Paphos districts.
PROPERTY_DAMAGE: Extensive damages in flooded premises and vehicles in flooded roadways.
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: The amount of rainfall recorded in the 24 hour period between 31/10-1/11/2016 in many stations was was more than double the mean value for the whole month of October. Many flood damages in Larnaca, but also in Limassol and Paphos districts.Fire department was called for help in 75 episodes.Premises flooded. Roads closed by flash floods and people were trapped inside their vehicles.

PLACE: Larnaca, Pano Panayia, Drinia, Farmakas, Agios Neophytos
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: The 24hr rainfall in affected locations was well above the mean monthly total for the whole month. e.g. at Pano Panayia 53.6mmm whereas mean monthly total is 47.6mm. Roadways were flooded and closed to traffic. In some places considerable settlement of road pavements occurred. There were land slides in Paphos district. Flooding of urban or rural premises caused big damages to properties. Many vehicles were swept away and suffered extreme damages by flash floods. Peoples' lives were in some places jeopardized. Some streams overfloated. The fire department responded to hundreds of episodes all over the island. In some cases the Civil Defense was called in for help. Branches were cut off trees or whole trees were uprooted by the severity of storms. Extensive damages to farming and agriculture were reported. Power outages           occurred in some areas.

The 24hr rainfall in most of the affected areas was, was more than double the mean for the whole month. Roads and premises flooded. Roadways blocked by debris and flood-water and people trapped in their vehicles. Fire department intervened in 75 cases to rescue people and pump water from flooded roads and premises. Extensive damages to crops and farming in affected rural areas. Some disruptions in power supply.

TOTAL_DAMAGE: Several roads were closed for hours

DETAILED_LOCATION: Secteur de Porto-Vecchio. D659 (route d'Arca), D468 (route de l'Osu), D168 (entre Favona et Conca), D268 (route de Bavilla). D159 (Muratello), D59 (Lévie), D 859 (de Porto-Vecchio à Sota), portions de la RT10.
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Les cumuls de pluie depuis le début de l'épisode pluvieux ont provoqué des inondations et coupures de voies de circulation sur le secteur de Porto-Vecchio. Le 22/01 en milieu d'après-midi, une famille devait être relogée à Porto-Vecchio, les routes d'Arca et de l'Osu ainsi que la D168 entre Favona et Conca sont inondées et coupées à la circulation. Un éboulement obstrue la route de Bavella. Les D159, D59 (Lévie), D 859 (de Porto-Vecchio à Sota) et la RT10 (portions) étaient également inondées. Le 23, un homme en scooter est retrouvé mort sur la D659.

DETAILED_LOCATION: Mainly Paphos district, but many locations throughout the island were affected during the period 10-13/32017
EVENT_DESCRIPTION: Very high rainfall amounts throughout the island for the period 10-13/3/2017, as compared to the normal mean monthly total. Total rainfall ranged from 40 to 47mm in 24 hrs in many places. Many areas and premises flooded island wide and various damages to properties were reported.Human lives were endangered in some cases. Trees were uprooted and transport routes closed down.The fire brigade responded to 86 calls for help and for pumping water from flooded premises and city streets.
